3.00	Hoapili	Hoapili	Ulumāheihei Hoapili (c. 1775–1840) was a member of the nobility during the formation of the Kingdom of Hawaii. He was a trusted military and political advisor to King Kamehameha I, known as "Kamehameha the Great". Although trusted with one of the last symbolic rites of the Hawaiian religion, he later became a supporter of Christian missionaries.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Hoapili_1839_signature.svg/125px-Hoapili_1839_signature.svg.png
